 no easy answers to the question of how to confront systematic inequality on a global scale. But the first step, Robbins suggests, is to acknowledge that we are, in fact, beneficiaries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aCosmopolitanismxPhilosophy. 0aEqualityxPhilosophy. 0aHuman rightsxPhilosophy. 0aHumanitarianismxPhilosophy. 0aSocial justicexPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2017z978311069634940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822372172zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822372172423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822372172.jpg  a978-3-11-069634-9  DUK eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles